30/11/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Upper House of the BiH Parliament adopted the draft defence law in its first reading Saturday (29 November). 
The Upper House also passed related amendments to the law on the BiH Council of Ministers and the law on ministries. 
Enes Becirbasic, Secretary General of the BiH Standing Committee for Military Matters, revealed hopes that the House of Representatives would adopt the defence law and the amendments Monday, sending a positive message to NATO.The legislation would establish a centralised military command -- the major pre-condition for joining the Partnership for Peace programme. 
(FENA, SRNA, BBC - 29/11/03)
